I am a student, and as part of my second year I have to undertake a placement. I had an interview in London at 9:00, and I didn't realise that the travel cards were nearly £30 before 9... WITH my railcard. Well when I asked the man for one and he gave that price I nearly cried, I don't have much money as it is and that was most of my weekly budget gone. He then turned around to me and said "that's why you get a job", which was incredibly rude and made me feel even worse about the fact that I now had a massive, unforseen dent in my budget.

Long story short, I encountered rude staff and INSANELY expensive tickets. I beg of the train companies to fix these prices PLEASE, and make them more accessible. It's unrealistic to think that anyone can afford this, especially people in my situation who don't have very much money but still have to do day to day things.
It's great lots of low price food and the week on offer thinks for the house and tool kits I been going there for years and still will .gillingham

ticket machine works when it wants to. once i had to buy another ticket to make it to work on time because there was no staf around.
they were also very quick to fine me when i lost my ticket. absolutely dissapointed to be honest

I tried 3 stations today in the mornig to buy a weekly train ticket in advance Weds start date, strood chatham and Rochester I was told no the machine does not allow you to.  They are quick to give you a fine if you do not travel with a bought ticket. Staff tried the stand alone machine it does not allow you to either. Staffs tried on line no joy.poor service high speed crowded no seat and the tickt is expensive. Trains always late and dirty. The sooner they nationallise this service the better. Overseas competition needed ASAP. Bad weather no trains and we get no pay for not going to work its a joke.
